Product Knowledge Quiz – Study Material

Title: Core Banking Compliance and Security Basics
Audience: Branch and operations staff
Purpose: Prepare for the 10-question product knowledge quiz

1) KYC (Know Your Customer)
- KYC is the process of verifying customer identity.
- Objective: prevent fraud, impersonation, and financial crime.
- Typical KYC documents: National ID, valid proof of address, and supporting account-opening data.

2) Role of Compliance
- Compliance teams verify identity documentation and monitor adherence to regulations.
- They ensure policies align with AML/CFT and internal control standards.

3) AML Controls
- AML means Anti-Money Laundering.
- Purpose: detect and prevent suspicious transactions and illegal fund flows.
- Staff should escalate unusual patterns through approved channels.

4) Acceptable Proof of Identity
- A National ID card is commonly accepted as primary ID.
- Supporting documents may be needed based on product and risk category.

5) Account Closure Requests
- First step: verify the customer/account holder identity.
- Then follow closure SOP, check pending obligations, and process with approvals.

6) OTP Security
- OTP stands for One Time Password.
- Used for transaction authentication and secure access.
- OTP must never be shared with anyone.

7) Suspicious Transaction Handling
- Do not ignore or process silently.
- Record relevant details and report through the approved escalation process immediately.

8) Information Security Goal
- Protect confidentiality, integrity, and availability (CIA) of data.
- Use least-privilege access and secure handling of customer information.

9) Strong Password Practice
- Use uppercase + lowercase + numbers + symbols.
- Avoid predictable content (name, birth year, repeated digits).
- Rotate and protect credentials as per policy.

10) Why Periodic Quizzes Matter
- Reinforces product understanding and policy compliance.
- Improves customer guidance quality and reduces operational risk.

Quick Revision Checklist
- KYC meaning and purpose
- Compliance role in document verification
- AML objective
- Identity proof examples
- Account closure first action
- OTP full form and safe usage
- Suspicious transaction response
- CIA triad in infosec
- Strong password components
- Purpose of periodic knowledge testing

End of Study Material